## Vulnerability Report

**PII Disclosure via Unauthenticated JavascriptInterface: getAadCurrentUser() and getDeviceId() in StreamPlayerView**

**Vulnerability Type:** Information Disclosure / Sensitive Data Exposure

**Affected File:**
- `teams_java/sources/com/microsoft/skype/teams/calling/view/StreamPlayerView.java` (lines ~175-185 and ~237-243)

**Vulnerability Description:**

`StreamPlayerView` exposes two `@JavascriptInterface` methods on the `NativeInterface` object that leak identity and device information to any JavaScript running in the WebView, without any authentication check or origin verification:

**`getAadCurrentUser()`** (line ~175):
```java
@JavascriptInterface
public String getAadCurrentUser() {
    StreamPlayerView streamPlayerView = StreamPlayerView.this;
    StringBuilder sb = new StringBuilder("{\"oid\":\"");
    sb.append(streamPlayerView.mUserObjectId);  // AAD Object ID (GUID)
    sb.append("\",\"tid\":\"");
    sb.append(streamPlayerView.mUserTenantId);  // Tenant ID (GUID)
    sb.append("\",\"upn\":\"");
    return MusicViewState$$ExternalSyntheticOutline0.m(sb, streamPlayerView.mUserPrincipalName, "\"}");
    // Returns: {"oid":"<oid>","tid":"<tid>","upn":"<email@domain.com>"}
}
```

**`getDeviceId()`** (line ~237):
```java
@JavascriptInterface
public String getDeviceId() {
    return ((DeviceIdProvider) streamPlayerView.mDeviceIdProvider).getAndroidDeviceId();
}
```

**`getCallGuid()`** (line ~230) also leaks the internal call session identifier.

**Data leaked:**
- User's AAD Object ID (stable cross-service identifier — can be used in Microsoft Graph API to query all user data)
- Tenant ID (identifies the organization)
- User Principal Name / email address (direct PII)
