## Vulnerability Report

**Pre-fetch Broadcast Sent to Other Packages with Attacker-Controlled URL (Confused Deputy)**

**File:** `m365-decompiled/sources/com/microsoft/office/onepipe/g.java` (lines ~130-145)

**Vulnerability:** The OAS (OneDrive Activity Service) push notification handler (`g.java`) extracts the document URL (`du` field) from the push payload and broadcasts an `ACTION_NOTIFICATION_RECEIVED` intent to another Microsoft Office app package (Word, Excel, PowerPoint) with the URL as an extra. The target package is determined by the file extension (`itemExt` field), both of which come directly from the push payload without validation.

**Vulnerable code:**
```java
String lowerCase = strSubstring.toLowerCase();  // strSubstring = bundle.getString("itemExt")
if (applicationContext != null) {
    Map map = com.microsoft.office.appwarmup.util.a.a;  // extension -> AppType map
    if (map.containsKey(lowerCase)) {
        Intent intent = new Intent();
        int iIntValue = map.containsKey(lowerCase) ? ((Integer) map.get(lowerCase)).intValue() : 100;
        intent.putExtra("Url", fVar.b);  // fVar.b = bundle.getString("du") - ATTACKER CONTROLLED
        intent.putExtra("PayloadSenderIdentifier", 0);
        intent.putExtra("AppType", iIntValue);
        intent.putExtra("PackageName", applicationContext.getPackageName());
        intent.setAction("com.microsoft.office.appwarmup.action.NOTIFICATION_RECEIVED");
        intent.setPackage(ApplicationPackageHelper.GetApplicationPackageForAppType(applicationContext, iIntValue));
        applicationContext.sendBroadcast(intent);
    }
