## Vulnerability Report

## HolographicAnnotationsWebView: JS Bridge Exposed from Local Asset File with No Cross-Origin Restrictions Verification

**Vulnerability**: `HolographicAnnotationsWebView` loads `file:///android_asset/holographicStage.html` and registers `this` (the view itself) as the `"AndroidBridge"` JavaScript interface via `addJavascriptInterface(this, "AndroidBridge")`. The WebSettings do not explicitly set `setAllowUniversalAccessFromFileURLs`, `setAllowFileAccessFromFileURLs`, or `setAllowContentAccess` to safe values.

**Code** (`HolographicAnnotationsWebView.java` lines ~63-90):
```java
WebSettings settings = getSettings();
settings.setJavaScriptEnabled(true);
settings.setUseWideViewPort(true);
settings.setLoadWithOverviewMode(true);
// Note: setAllowUniversalAccessFromFileURLs NOT explicitly set to false
// Note: setAllowFileAccess NOT explicitly set to false
// Note: setAllowContentAccess NOT explicitly set to false
loadUrl("file:///android_asset/holographicStage.html");
addJavascriptInterface(this, "AndroidBridge");
```

Compare: `AnnotationWebView.java` explicitly sets:
```java
settings.setAllowUniversalAccessFromFileURLs(false);
settings.setAllowFileAccess(false);
settings.setAllowFileAccessFromFileURLs(false);
settings.setAllowContentAccess(true);
```

`HolographicAnnotationsWebView` sets none of these, relying on Android defaults (which vary by API level and may allow cross-origin file access on older devices).

**Bridge Methods Exposed** (all callable from any JS on the file:// page):
- `startInking(int requestId, float x, float y, long timestamp)` — forwards to data channel with participant ID
- `continueInking(int requestId, float[] x, float[] y)` — forwards ink stroke data
- `stopInking(int requestId)` — stops ink stroke
- `placeArrow(int, float, float, long)` / `placeDirectionalArrow(int, float, float, long, float)` — place annotations
- `deleteAnnotations(int[] requestIds, boolean)` — deletes annotations from the call
- `recoverAnnotations(int[] requestIds)` — recovers annotations
- `requestClearAnnotationBehavior()` — spawns AlertDialog (UI thread, callable repeatedly = DoS)
- `stopAnnotations()` — stops annotation session entirely
- `debugLog(String str)` — writes arbitrary strings to log

**Static State Pollution**:
- `HolographicAnnotationsWebView.highestObservedRequestId` — static int, shared across ALL sessions
- `HolographicAnnotationsWebView.numberOfSelfAnnotationsFromAllSessions` — static int, shared across ALL sessions
- `HolographicAnnotationsWebView.lastUsedColorIndex` — static int, shared across ALL sessions

If an attacker loads external content (via a compromised `holographicStage.html` or a same-origin redirect if universal file access is enabled), they can manipulate shared static counters affecting other sessions. Additionally, `requestClearAnnotationBehavior()` creates an AlertDialog on the UI thread without rate limiting — repeated calls cause UI spam (DoS).

