{"valid":true,"title":"Misconfigured iframe Sandbox: `allow-scripts` + `allow-same-origin` Enables Sandbox Escape in Teams iOS Designer WebView","summary":"The Teams iOS app embeds the Microsoft Designer experience inside an iframe created by the `vt` class (`createAppFrame()` method). The production configuration (`kt()` function) explicitly sets `disableEmbeddedCSPEnforcement: true` and `enableSandboxing: true`. This means the iframe's `csp` attribute is never applied (the CSP short-circuits via `||` when `disableEmbeddedCSPEnforcement` is truthy), and the sandbox is applied with the dangerous combination of both `allow-scripts` and `allow-same-origin`.

