{"valid":true,"title":"BluetoothBroadcastReceiver Exported Without Permission - Any App Can Trigger Dock Mode Registration","summary":"The `BluetoothBroadcastReceiver` in Microsoft Teams Android is declared in `AndroidManifest.xml` with `android:exported="true"` and **no `android:permission` guard**. It listens for `android.bluetooth.device.action.ACL_CONNECTED`. Any app installed on the device can send a broadcast with this action and trigger the receiver.

When triggered, `BluetoothBroadcastReceiver.onMAMReceive()` (lines ~20-40) checks if `mStateChangeBroadcastReceiver` is null (it is, on first spoofed broadcast) and then:
