An attacker who can influence the RN JS bundle — or who exploits any of the existing RN bridge entry points (e.g., via the `PreWarmedRNCWebViewManager` view's `source` prop) — can create a `PreWarmedRNCWebView` component with `source={{ html: '<script>...</script>', baseUrl: 'https://sharepoint.com' }}`. Android's WebView gives the loaded HTML document the same origin as the `baseUrl`, meaning the injected HTML runs with full same-origin privileges for `sharepoint.com`. The `PreWarmedRNCWebView` extends `RNCWebView`, which adds the `ReactNativeWebView` JavaScript bridge (via `addJavascriptInterface` or `addWebMessageListener` with wildcard `Set.of("*")` allowed origins), enabling the malicious WebView JS to post messages back into the RN application layer.

