// - account.userId (AAD Object ID)
// - account.tenantId (Azure AD Tenant ID)  
// - account.identityType (AAD/MSA)
// - account.isEUDB (data sovereignty flag)
// - hostAppConfig.hostCorrelationId (conversationId)
// - hostAppConfig.hostSessionId (userMessageId)
// - token (Designer access token — a Bearer token for designerappservice.officeapps.live.com)
return "window.dRunner.setupConfigIfNeeded(" + json.encodeToString(...) + ")";
```

**The Token Field**: `DesignerRunnerConfig.token` is the str2 parameter (`generateImageContent.imageGenerationPrompt`... wait, let me re-read: `new DesignerRunnerConfig(str2, str, ...)` — str2 is the prompt/token passed from the caller. Looking at the GenerateImageRenderer call: `DesignerSdkKt.DesignerSdk(str3, generateImageContent.imageGenerationPrompt, botMessage, ...)` — str2 is `imageGenerationPrompt`.)

**PII Data Flow**:
1. `ImageGenerationConfiguration.designerAppAccountInfo` contains userId and tenantId (from Teams user profile)
